Using the change of base formula, we can rewrite each logarithm in terms of $\log_2$. We get:

\begin{align*}
\log_2{3} &= \frac{\log_2{3}}{\log_2{2}} = \log_2{\sqrt{3}} \\
\log_3{4} &= \frac{\log_2{4}}{\log_2{3}} = 2\log_2{\frac{4}{3}} \\
\log_4{5} &= \frac{\log_2{5}}{\log_2{4}} = \log_2{\frac{5}{4}} \\
\log_5{6} &= \frac{\log_2{6}}{\log_2{5}} = \log_2{\frac{6}{5}} \\
\log_6{7} &= \frac{\log_2{7}}{\log_2{6}} = \log_2{\frac{7}{6}} \\
\log_7{8} &= \frac{\log_2{8}}{\log_2{7}} = 3\log_2{\frac{2}{7}}
\end{align*}

Multiplying all of these together, we get:

\begin{align*}
\log_2{\sqrt{3}} \cdot 2\log_2{\frac{4}{3}} \cdot \log_2{\frac{5}{4}} \cdot \log_2{\frac{6}{5}} \cdot \log_2{\frac{7}{6}} \cdot 3\log_2{\frac{2}{7}} &= 6\log_2{\frac{2}{7}} \cdot \log_2{\frac{4}{3}} \cdot \log_2{\frac{5}{4}} \cdot \log_2{\frac{6}{5}} \cdot \log_2{\sqrt{3}} \\
&= 6\log_2{\frac{2\sqrt{3}}{35}}
\end{align*}

Therefore, the value of the expression is $\boxed{6\log_2{\frac{2\sqrt{3}}{35}}}$.
